annotationA: Peroxisomal membrane protein 34, isoform A; Transporter activity; transmembrane transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transport; mitochondrial transport; Belongs to the mitochondrial carrier (TC 2.A.29) family
annotationB: Peroxin 3 (Pex3) is a peroxisomal membrane protein (PMP) involved in de novo peroxisome biogenesis from the ER and PMP import from the cytosol. Pex3 also facilitates the insertion of proteins into the membrane of mature peroxisomes via its interaction with the PMP chaperone Pex19
